             Akinari Horii , a former executive
director at the Bank of Japan, joined the Canon Institute for
Global Studies as an adviser on July 1.  
 The appointment was confirmed today by Rika Yabe, a
spokesman at the Tokyo-based research group. Former central bank
Governor  Toshihiko Fukui  is president of the institute, which is
chaired by Canon Inc.â€™s Chief Executive Officer  Fujio Mitarai .  
